b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe34065.htm)  [Next](sbe34067.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1417930306/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Vedanta Sutras, commentary by Sankaracharya (SBE34)_ , tr. by George\nThibaut [1890] at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\n29\\. On account of the manifestation, so \xc3\x82 _s_ marathya opines.\n\nThe circumstance of the highest Lord who transcends all measure being spoken\nof as measured by a span has for its reason 'manifestation.' The highest Lord\nmanifests\n\np. 151\n\nhimself as measured by a span, i.e. he specially manifests himself for the\nbenefit of his worshippers in some special places, such as the heart and the\nlike, where he may be perceived. Hence, according to the opinion of the\nteacher \xc3\x82 _s_ marathya, the scriptural passage which speaks of him who is\nmeasured by a span may refer to the highest Lord.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 2, 30](sbe34067.htm)\n\n"